[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837759026708&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837759026708&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

Right now, with our multiple small unregistered hosts sitting more-or-less
invisible behind registered host ALMSA-1, we're pretty much stuck with
the user%unreg@registered form because of some users having accounts on
multiple unregistered hosts.  We could, and did, use user@registered for a
while, but now "user" could be on more than one "unreg" (it defaults to a
preferred unreg if the "%unreg" is not present in the incoming address).
-Rich

